headline: Delta Air Lines (DAL) Profit Margins Slip Below Prior Year, Reinforcing Cautious Growth Narrative
summary: Delta Air Lines (DAL) posted net profit margins of 7.4%, just off last year’s 7.7% mark, and continued its profitability streak from the past five years with an impressive 73.2% annual earnings growth over that period. Despite high-quality earnings, the outlook is more cautious. Revenue is forecast to grow just 2.8% per year compared to the US market’s 10%, and earnings are expected to fall by 7.1% a year for the next three years. Margins remain solid, but softer growth and declining earnings...
